Note:
Runa Standard Library: Package Management and Site Packages Module

Production-grade package discovery, dependency resolution, and site-packages
management system. Competitive with Python's site module, Node.js's require
resolution, Go's module system, and Rust's cargo ecosystem.

Key Features:
- Package discovery across multiple search paths
- Version resolution and compatibility checking
- Dependency graph analysis and conflict detection
- Site-packages directory management
- Virtual environment support and isolation
- Package metadata extraction and validation
- AI/agent-friendly package interfaces
- Cross-platform package installation paths
- Development vs production package differentiation
- Real-time package monitoring and hot-reloading

Architecture:
Built on Runa's natural language primitives with optimized search algorithms
and caching for performance. Provides both simple package queries and
advanced dependency management for complex applications.
:End Note

Import "site/site" as Site
Import "../../collections" as Collections

Note: Core Package Management Types
Type called "PackageInfo":
    name as String
    version as String
    location as String
    description as String
    author as String
    dependencies as List[Dependency]
    dev_dependencies as List[Dependency]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]
    is_installed as Boolean
    install_time as Optional[Float]
    size_bytes as Optional[Integer]

Type called "Dependency":
    name as String
    version_requirement as String
    is_optional as Boolean
    is_dev_only as Boolean
    source as String
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "PackageSearchPaths":
    site_packages as List[String]
    user_packages as List[String]
    system_packages as List[String]
    virtual_env_packages as List[String]
    development_packages as List[String]
    custom_paths as List[String]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "VirtualEnvironment":
    name as String
    path as String
    python_version as Optional[String]
    runa_version as Optional[String]
    is_active as Boolean
    packages as List[PackageInfo]
    creation_time as Optional[Float]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "DependencyGraph":
    packages as Dictionary[String, PackageInfo]
    dependencies as Dictionary[String, List[String]]
    conflicts as List[DependencyConflict]
    resolution_order as List[String]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "DependencyConflict":
    package_name as String
    conflicting_versions as List[String]
    required_by as List[String]
    severity as String
    suggested_resolution as String
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type PackageResult is:
    | PackageSuccess with info as PackageInfo
    | PackageNotFound with searched_paths as List[String]
    | PackageError with error as String

Type SearchResult is:
    | SearchSuccess with packages as List[PackageInfo]
    | SearchFailure with error as String

Note: Primary Package Management Functions
Process called "find_package" that takes name as String and version as Optional[String] returns PackageResult:
    Note: Find package with optional version constraint
    Try:
        Let search_paths be get_package_search_paths
        Let searched_locations be list containing
        For each path_category in list containing search_paths.site_packages, search_paths.user_packages, search_paths.system_packages, search_paths.virtual_env_packages:
            For each search_path in path_category:
                Add search_path to searched_locations
                Let package_result be search_package_in_path with name as name and path as search_path and version as version
                Match package_result:
                    When PackageSuccess with info as package_info:
                        Return PackageSuccess with info as package_info
                    Otherwise:
                        Continue
        Return PackageNotFound with searched_paths as searched_locations
    Catch error:
        Return PackageError with error as "Package search failed: " + error.message

Process called "get_installed_packages" returns SearchResult:
    Note: Get list of all installed packages across all search paths
    Try:
        Let all_packages be list containing
        Let search_paths be get_package_search_paths
        Let all_search_paths be combine_search_paths with paths as search_paths
        For each search_path in all_search_paths:
            Let path_packages be scan_packages_in_path with path as search_path
            For each package in path_packages:
                Add package to all_packages
        Note: Remove duplicates and resolve conflicts
        Let unique_packages be deduplicate_packages with packages as all_packages
        Return SearchSuccess with packages as unique_packages
    Catch error:
        Return SearchFailure with error as "Failed to scan installed packages"

Process called "get_package_search_paths" returns PackageSearchPaths:
    Note: Get comprehensive package search paths for current environment
    Try:
        Let site_options be Site.create_site_options
        Let site_result be Site.get_site_info with options as site_options
        Match site_result:
            When Site.SiteSuccess with info as site_info:
                Let site_packages be build_site_packages_paths with site_info as site_info
                Let user_packages be build_user_packages_paths with site_info as site_info
                Let system_packages be build_system_packages_paths with site_info as site_info
                Let virtual_packages be detect_virtual_environment_packages
                Let dev_packages be detect_development_packages
                Let custom_packages be get_custom_package_paths
                Return PackageSearchPaths with:
                    site_packages as site_packages
                    user_packages as user_packages
                    system_packages as system_packages
                    virtual_env_packages as virtual_packages
                    development_packages as dev_packages
                    custom_paths as custom_packages
                    metadata as gather_search_paths_metadata with site_info as site_info
            When Site.SiteFailure with error as site_error:
                Return get_fallback_search_paths
    Catch error:
        Return get_fallback_search_paths

Process called "resolve_dependencies" that takes package as PackageInfo returns DependencyGraph:
    Note: Resolve dependency graph for package with conflict detection
    Try:
        Let graph be DependencyGraph with:
            packages as dictionary containing
            dependencies as dictionary containing
            conflicts as list containing
            resolution_order as list containing
            metadata as dictionary containing
        Let to_resolve be Collections.create_queue
        Collections.enqueue with queue as to_resolve and item as package.name
        Let visited be Collections.create_set
        While not Collections.is_queue_empty with queue as to_resolve:
            Let current_package_name be Collections.dequeue with queue as to_resolve
            If Collections.contains with set as visited and item as current_package_name:
                Continue
            Collections.add with set as visited and item as current_package_name
            Let current_package_result be find_package with name as current_package_name and version as None
            Match current_package_result:
                When PackageSuccess with info as current_info:
                    Set graph.packages at key current_package_name to current_info
                    Let dependency_names be list containing
                    For each dep in current_info.dependencies:
                        If not dep.is_optional:
                            Add dep.name to dependency_names
                            Collections.enqueue with queue as to_resolve and item as dep.name
                    Set graph.dependencies at key current_package_name to dependency_names
                When PackageNotFound with searched_paths as paths:
                    Let conflict be DependencyConflict with:
                        package_name as current_package_name
                        conflicting_versions as list containing
                        required_by as list containing package.name
                        severity as "error"
                        suggested_resolution as "Install missing package: " + current_package_name
                        metadata as dictionary containing
                    Add conflict to graph.conflicts
                Otherwise:
                    Continue
        Let resolution_order be topological_sort_dependencies with graph as graph
        Set graph.resolution_order to resolution_order
        Return graph
    Catch error:
        Return DependencyGraph with:
            packages as dictionary containing
            dependencies as dictionary containing
            conflicts as list containing
            resolution_order as list containing
            metadata as dictionary containing "error" as error.message

Process called "get_virtual_environments" returns List[VirtualEnvironment]:
    Note: Discover and analyze virtual environments
    Try:
        Let virtual_envs be list containing
        Note: Check common virtual environment locations
        Let venv_paths be list containing:
            "~/.virtualenvs",
            "~/.conda/envs",
            "~/miniconda3/envs",
            "~/anaconda3/envs",
            "./venv",
            "./.venv",
            "./env",
            "./.env"
        For each venv_path in venv_paths:
            Let expanded_path be Site.expand_user_path with path as venv_path
            Let venvs_in_path be scan_virtual_environments_in_path with path as expanded_path
            For each venv in venvs_in_path:
                Add venv to virtual_envs
        Note: Check environment variables for active virtual environment
        Let virtual_env_path be Site.get_environment_variable with name as "VIRTUAL_ENV"
        If virtual_env_path is not None:
            Let active_venv be analyze_virtual_environment with path as virtual_env_path and is_active as true
            If active_venv is not None:
                Add active_venv to virtual_envs
        Return virtual_envs
    Catch error:
        Return list containing

Process called "create_package_manifest" that takes packages as List[PackageInfo] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Create comprehensive package manifest for reproducible environments
    Try:
        Let manifest be dictionary containing
        Set manifest at key "generator" to "runa-site-packages"
        Set manifest at key "version" to "1.0.0"
        Set manifest at key "created_at" to Site.get_current_timestamp
        Let platform_info be dictionary containing
        Let site_options be Site.create_site_options
        Let site_result be Site.get_site_info with options as site_options
        Match site_result:
            When Site.SiteSuccess with info as site_info:
                Set platform_info at key "platform" to site_info.platform
                Set platform_info at key "architecture" to site_info.architecture
                Set platform_info at key "runa_version" to site_info.runa_version
            Otherwise:
                Set platform_info at key "platform" to "unknown"
                Set platform_info at key "architecture" to "unknown"
                Set platform_info at key "runa_version" to None
        Set manifest at key "platform" to platform_info
        Let package_entries be dictionary containing
        For each package in packages:
            Let package_entry be dictionary containing
            Set package_entry at key "version" to package.version
            Set package_entry at key "location" to package.location
            Set package_entry at key "dependencies" to convert_dependencies_to_dict with deps as package.dependencies
            Set package_entry at key "install_time" to package.install_time
            Set package_entry at key "size_bytes" to package.size_bytes
            Set package_entries at key package.name to package_entry
        Set manifest at key "packages" to package_entries
        Let dependency_graph be create_global_dependency_graph with packages as packages
        Set manifest at key "dependency_tree" to serialize_dependency_graph with graph as dependency_graph
        Return manifest
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing "error" as "Failed to create package manifest"

Note: Package Discovery and Analysis Functions
Process called "search_package_in_path" that takes name as String and path as String and version as Optional[String] returns PackageResult:
    Note: Search for specific package in given path
    Try:
        Let package_dir be Site.join_paths with base as path and component as name
        Let package_exists be Site.check_directory_exists with path as package_dir
        If package_exists:
            Let package_info be analyze_package_directory with path as package_dir and name as name
            If version is not None:
                If is_version_compatible with required as version and available as package_info.version:
                    Return PackageSuccess with info as package_info
                Otherwise:
                    Return PackageNotFound with searched_paths as list containing path
            Otherwise:
                Return PackageSuccess with info as package_info
        Otherwise:
            Note: Check for package files (e.g., name.runa, name.toml)
            Let package_file_candidates be list containing:
                Site.join_paths with base as path and component as (name plus ".runa"),
                Site.join_paths with base as path and component as (name plus ".toml"),
                Site.join_paths with base as path and component as (name plus ".json")
            For each candidate_file in package_file_candidates:
                Let file_exists be Site.check_file_exists with path as candidate_file
                If file_exists:
                    Let package_info be analyze_package_file with path as candidate_file and name as name
                    Return PackageSuccess with info as package_info
            Return PackageNotFound with searched_paths as list containing path
    Catch error:
        Return PackageError with error as "Failed to search package in path: " path

Process called "scan_packages_in_path" that takes path as String returns List[PackageInfo]:
    Note: Scan all packages in given path
    Try:
        Let packages be list containing
        Let path_exists be Site.check_directory_exists with path as path
        If not path_exists:
            Return packages
        Let directory_contents be list_directory_contents with path as path
        For each entry in directory_contents:
            Let entry_path be Site.join_paths with base as path and component as entry.name
            If entry.is_directory:
                Let package_info be analyze_package_directory with path as entry_path and name as entry.name
                If package_info is not None:
                    Add package_info to packages
            Otherwise if entry.name ends with ".runa" or entry.name ends with ".toml":
                Let package_name be extract_package_name_from_filename with filename as entry.name
                Let package_info be analyze_package_file with path as entry_path and name as package_name
                If package_info is not None:
                    Add package_info to packages
        Return packages
    Catch error:
        Return list containing

Process called "analyze_package_directory" that takes path as String and name as String returns Optional[PackageInfo]:
    Note: Analyze package directory structure and extract metadata
    Try:
        Let manifest_candidates be list containing:
            Site.join_paths with base as path and component as "runa.toml",
            Site.join_paths with base as path and component as "package.toml",
            Site.join_paths with base as path and component as "package.json",
            Site.join_paths with base as path and component as "__init__.runa"
        For each manifest_file in manifest_candidates:
            Let file_exists be Site.check_file_exists with path as manifest_file
            If file_exists:
                Let package_info be parse_package_manifest with path as manifest_file and name as name and location as path
                If package_info is not None:
                    Return Some with value as package_info
        Note: Fallback to basic directory analysis
        Let basic_info be create_basic_package_info with name as name and location as path
        Return Some with value as basic_info
    Catch error:
        Return None

Process called "analyze_package_file" that takes path as String and name as String returns Optional[PackageInfo]:
    Note: Analyze single package file and extract metadata
    Try:
        Let file_content be Site.read_file_content with path as path
        If file_content is None:
            Return None
        If path ends with ".toml":
            Return parse_toml_package_info with content as file_content and name as name and location as path
        Otherwise if path ends with ".json":
            Return parse_json_package_info with content as file_content and name as name and location as path
        Otherwise if path ends with ".runa":
            Return parse_runa_package_info with content as file_content and name as name and location as path
        Return None
    Catch error:
        Return None

Note: Virtual Environment Management
Process called "scan_virtual_environments_in_path" that takes path as String returns List[VirtualEnvironment]:
    Note: Scan for virtual environments in given path
    Try:
        Let virtual_envs be list containing
        Let path_exists be Site.check_directory_exists with path as path
        If not path_exists:
            Return virtual_envs
        Let directory_contents be list_directory_contents with path as path
        For each entry in directory_contents:
            If entry.is_directory:
                Let venv_path be Site.join_paths with base as path and component as entry.name
                Let venv_info be analyze_virtual_environment with path as venv_path and is_active as false
                If venv_info is not None:
                    Add venv_info to virtual_envs
        Return virtual_envs
    Catch error:
        Return list containing

Process called "analyze_virtual_environment" that takes path as String and is_active as Boolean returns Optional[VirtualEnvironment]:
    Note: Analyze virtual environment structure and metadata
    Try:
        Note: Check for virtual environment indicators
        Let indicators be list containing:
            Site.join_paths with base as path and component as "pyvenv.cfg",
            Site.join_paths with base as path and component as "bin/activate",
            Site.join_paths with base as path and component as "Scripts/activate.bat",
            Site.join_paths with base as path and component as "lib",
            Site.join_paths with base as path and component as "Lib"
        Let is_venv be false
        For each indicator in indicators:
            Let exists be Site.check_file_exists with path as indicator
            If exists:
                Set is_venv to true
                Break
        If not is_venv:
            Return None
        Let venv_name be extract_directory_name_from_path with path as path
        Let packages be scan_virtual_environment_packages with venv_path as path
        Let creation_time be get_directory_creation_time with path as path
        Let python_version be detect_virtual_environment_python_version with path as path
        Let runa_version be detect_virtual_environment_runa_version with path as path
        Return Some with value as VirtualEnvironment with:
            name as venv_name
            path as path
            python_version as python_version
            runa_version as runa_version
            is_active as is_active
            packages as packages
            creation_time as creation_time
            metadata as gather_virtual_environment_metadata with path as path
    Catch error:
        Return None

Note: Dependency Resolution and Graph Analysis
Process called "topological_sort_dependencies" that takes graph as DependencyGraph returns List[String]:
    Note: Topologically sort dependencies to determine installation order
    Try:
        Let sorted_packages be list containing
        Let in_degree be dictionary containing
        Let packages_queue be Collections.create_queue
        Note: Calculate in-degrees
        For each package_name in keys of graph.packages:
            Set in_degree at key package_name to 0
        For each package_name in keys of graph.dependencies:
            For each dependency in graph.dependencies[package_name]:
                If in_degree contains key dependency:
                    Let current_degree be in_degree[dependency]
                    Set in_degree at key dependency to (current_degree + 1)
                Otherwise:
                    Set in_degree at key dependency to 1
        Note: Add packages with no dependencies to queue
        For each package_name in keys of in_degree:
            If in_degree[package_name] is equal to 0:
                Collections.enqueue with queue as packages_queue and item as package_name
        Note: Process packages in topological order
        While not Collections.is_queue_empty with queue as packages_queue:
            Let current_package be Collections.dequeue with queue as packages_queue
            Add current_package to sorted_packages
            If graph.dependencies contains key current_package:
                For each dependency in graph.dependencies[current_package]:
                    Let current_degree be in_degree[dependency]
                    Set in_degree at key dependency to (current_degree - 1)
                    If in_degree[dependency] is equal to 0:
                        Collections.enqueue with queue as packages_queue and item as dependency
        Note: Check for circular dependencies
        If length of sorted_packages is not equal to length of keys of graph.packages:
            Note: Circular dependency detected, return partial order
            Return sorted_packages
        Return sorted_packages
    Catch error:
        Return list containing

Process called "deduplicate_packages" that takes packages as List[PackageInfo] returns List[PackageInfo]:
    Note: Remove duplicate packages, preferring newer versions
    Try:
        Let package_map be dictionary containing
        For each package in packages:
            If package_map contains key package.name:
                Let existing_package be package_map[package.name]
                If is_version_newer with new_version as package.version and old_version as existing_package.version:
                    Set package_map at key package.name to package
            Otherwise:
                Set package_map at key package.name to package
        Let unique_packages be list containing
        For each package_name in keys of package_map:
            Add package_map[package_name] to unique_packages
        Return unique_packages
    Catch error:
        Return packages

Note: Path Building and Configuration Functions
Process called "build_site_packages_paths" that takes site_info as Site.SiteInfo returns List[String]:
    Note: Build site-packages paths based on platform
    Try:
        Let paths be list containing
        Match site_info.platform:
            When "windows":
                Add Site.join_paths with base as site_info.site_data_dir and component as "site-packages" to paths
                Add "C:\\Program Files\\Runa\\site-packages" to paths
                Add "C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Runa\\site-packages" to paths
            When "macos":
                Add Site.join_paths with base as site_info.site_data_dir and component as "site-packages" to paths
                Add "/usr/local/lib/runa/site-packages" to paths
                Add "/System/Library/Frameworks/Runa.framework/site-packages" to paths
            Otherwise:
                Add Site.join_paths with base as site_info.site_data_dir and component as "site-packages" to paths
                Add "/usr/local/lib/runa/site-packages" to paths
                Add "/usr/lib/runa/site-packages" to paths
                Add "/opt/runa/site-packages" to paths
        Return paths
    Catch error:
        Return list containing

Process called "build_user_packages_paths" that takes site_info as Site.SiteInfo returns List[String]:
    Note: Build user packages paths based on platform
    Try:
        Let paths be list containing
        Add Site.join_paths with base as site_info.user_data_dir and component as "packages" to paths
        Add Site.join_paths with base as site_info.user_data_dir and component as "site-packages" to paths
        Match site_info.platform:
            When "windows":
                Let appdata be Site.get_environment_variable with name as "APPDATA"
                If appdata is not None:
                    Add Site.join_paths with base as appdata and component as "Runa\\packages" to paths
            Otherwise:
                Let home be Site.get_user_home_directory
                Add Site.join_paths with base as home and component as ".local/lib/runa/site-packages" to paths
                Add Site.join_paths with base as home and component as ".runa/packages" to paths
        Return paths
    Catch error:
        Return list containing

Note: Utility and Helper Functions
Process called "is_version_compatible" that takes required as String and available as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if available version satisfies required version constraint
    Try:
        Note: Simple version matching for now - can be enhanced with semver
        If required is equal to "*" or required is equal to "":
            Return true
        If required starts with ">=":
            Let required_version be substring with text as required and start as 2 and end as length of required
            Return is_version_greater_or_equal with version1 as available and version2 as required_version
        If required starts with ">":
            Let required_version be substring with text as required and start as 1 and end as length of required
            Return is_version_greater with version1 as available and version2 as required_version
        If required starts with "<=":
            Let required_version be substring with text as required and start as 2 and end as length of required
            Return is_version_less_or_equal with version1 as available and version2 as required_version
        If required starts with "<":
            Let required_version be substring with text as required and start as 1 and end as length of required
            Return is_version_less with version1 as available and version2 as required_version
        If required starts with "==":
            Let required_version be substring with text as required and start as 2 and end as length of required
            Return available is equal to required_version
        Note: Exact match by default
        Return available is equal to required
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "is_version_newer" that takes new_version as String and old_version as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Compare versions to determine if new_version is newer than old_version
    Try:
        Let new_parts be split_version_string with version as new_version
        Let old_parts be split_version_string with version as old_version
        Let max_length be max with a as length of new_parts and b as length of old_parts
        For i from 0 to (max_length - 1):
            Let new_part be 0
            Let old_part be 0
            If i is less than length of new_parts:
                Let parsed_new be parse_integer with text as new_parts[i]
                If parsed_new is not None:
                    Set new_part to parsed_new
            If i is less than length of old_parts:
                Let parsed_old be parse_integer with text as old_parts[i]
                If parsed_old is not None:
                    Set old_part to parsed_old
            If new_part is greater than old_part:
                Return true
            Otherwise if new_part is less than old_part:
                Return false
        Return false
        Note: Versions are equal
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "split_version_string" that takes version as String returns List[String]:
    Note: Split version string into components
    Try:
        Let clean_version be Site.trim_whitespace with text as version
        Let parts be list containing
        Let current_part be ""
        For each character in clean_version:
            If character is equal to ".":
                If current_part is not equal to "":
                    Add current_part to parts
                Set current_part to ""
            Otherwise:
                Set current_part to current_part plus character
        If current_part is not equal to "":
            Add current_part to parts
        Return parts
    Catch error:
        Return list containing "0"

